        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Fix Codex monthly credit limit display",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Parse and propagate Codex monthly credit limits from Codex CLI, OAuth, and OpenAI dashboard payloads.\n- Prefer the monthly credit limit when rendering credits in the menu, CLI output, and widget snapshots.\n- Let auto mode fall back from an OAuth zero-balance partial result to the Codex CLI so monthly credit limits are not hidden.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nCodex auto mode stopped at an OAuth credits response that contained `remaining = 0` but omitted the monthly credit limit. That prevented the later CLI source from returning the actual enterprise monthly credit limit.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `swift test --filter CodexOAuthCreditLimitTests`\n- `make check`\n- Verified packaged app output with `CodexBarCLI usage --provider codex --source auto` showing `source = codex-cli` and non-zero monthly credits.\n",
